---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Handshake — Trust Infrastructure for Agent-to-Agent Interactions"
  description="Authorization tells you what's allowed. Handshake tells you what's trusted. The mutual trust ceremony for the agent economy."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="hs-hero">
    <div class="hs-hero-eyebrow">What We're Building</div>
    <h1 class="hs-hero-title">
      Authorization tells you what's allowed.<br>
      <span class="hs-hero-title-em">Handshake tells you what's trusted.</span>
    </h1>
    <p class="hs-hero-sub">
      The mutual trust ceremony for agent-to-agent interactions — the moment
      where both sides verify each other before consequence, and where human
      override remains real, not ceremonial.
    </p>
    <form class="hs-waitlist-form" id="waitlist-form" data-endpoint="/api/waitlist">
      <div class="hs-waitlist-row">
        <input
          type="email"
          name="email"
          required
          placeholder="you@company.com"
          class="hs-waitlist-input"
          autocomplete="email"
        />
        <button type="submit" class="cta-link cta-link--primary hs-waitlist-btn">
          Join the waitlist
        </button>
      </div>
      <p class="hs-waitlist-status" id="waitlist-status" aria-live="polite"></p>
    </form>
  </section>

  <!-- Problem -->
  <section class="hs-section">
    <div class="hs-section-label">The Problem</div>
    <div class="hs-prose">
      <h2>The problem is not capability. It is accountability.</h2>
      <p>
        Agents are becoming capable of consequential action — booking travel, executing trades,
        sending communications, managing infrastructure. The models are getting smarter fast.
        But the governance layer has not kept pace.
      </p>
      <p>
        When an agent acts, who is accountable? The model doesn't know. The API it calls doesn't
        know. The system that issued it a token checked whether it was <strong>allowed</strong> —
        but allowed and <strong>trusted</strong> are different questions.
      </p>
      <div class="hs-distinction">
        <div class="hs-distinction-item">
          <span class="hs-distinction-label">Allowed</span>
          <p>A permission check. Does this agent have a token that grants access? Static. Determined at configuration time. Doesn't change based on behavior.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="hs-distinction-divider" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <div class="hs-distinction-item">
          <span class="hs-distinction-label hs-distinction-label--accent">Trusted</span>
          <p>A standing check. Given who this agent is, who it represents, and what it has done — should it be trusted to act right now? Dynamic. Earned through behavior. Forfeitable.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How it works -->
  <section class="hs-section">
    <div class="hs-section-label">How It Works</div>
    <div class="hs-prose">
      <h2>The three-phase mutual handshake</h2>
      <p>
        Before any consequential agent-to-agent transaction, both sides verify each other.
        Neither trusts blindly. The ceremony produces a signed artifact that the transaction
        system can verify offline — no round-trip to Handshake required.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="hs-phases">
      <div class="hs-phase">
        <span class="hs-phase-num">01</span>
        <h3 class="hs-phase-title">Verification</h3>
        <p class="hs-phase-desc">
          Both agents check each other's passport and standing. The customer agent calls
          <code>check_standing</code> on the merchant. The merchant presents its passport
          in the challenge. Scam agents — no standing, no history, no valid passport — are
          exposed before credentials are exchanged.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="hs-phase">
        <span class="hs-phase-num">02</span>
        <h3 class="hs-phase-title">Authorization</h3>
        <p class="hs-phase-desc">
          The customer agent calls <code>request_authorization</code>. Handshake evaluates
          both standings, applies policy, and either issues a signed artifact or escalates
          to the human principal. The principal can approve, deny, or approve with tighter
          scope constraints.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="hs-phase">
        <span class="hs-phase-num">03</span>
        <h3 class="hs-phase-title">Transaction</h3>
        <p class="hs-phase-desc">
          The customer agent presents the signed artifact to the merchant. The merchant calls
          <code>verifyArtifact</code> — two functions, offline, no Handshake call. The artifact
          carries both identities, both standings, and the authorized scope. The transaction proceeds.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Architecture -->
  <section class="hs-section">
    <div class="hs-section-label">Architecture</div>
    <div class="hs-prose">
      <h2>Passport, standing, ceremony</h2>
      <p>
        A real passport is worth understanding precisely, because it maps to how Handshake works
        in every important detail.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="hs-arch-grid">
      <div class="hs-arch-item">
        <h3>Agent Passport</h3>
        <p>
          Cryptographically signed identity document. Binds agent to principal, carries policy
          profile and approval thresholds. Issued by Handshake, not self-asserted. Versioned
          to prevent downgrade attacks. Revocable immediately.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="hs-arch-item">
        <h3>Standing</h3>
        <p>
          Behavioral trust score computed fresh on every request. Weighted from action history —
          risk tier, amount factor, outcome. One catastrophic denial collapses a high score.
          Trust is slow to earn, fast to lose.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="hs-arch-item">
        <h3>Human-in-the-Loop</h3>
        <p>
          When trust is uncertain, the principal is asked. Not a fallback — a first-class
          architectural boundary. Scope overrides let the principal tighten the artifact
          at approval time. Timeout fails closed.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Stack position -->
  <section class="hs-section">
    <div class="hs-section-label">Where It Sits</div>
    <div class="hs-prose">
      <h2>The layer that doesn't exist yet</h2>
      <p>
        The agent authorization market is forming. Most of it is commodity. Handshake sits
        between permission and action — the layer where "allowed" becomes "trusted" — and
        that layer currently has no owner.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="hs-stack">
      <div class="hs-stack-row">
        <span class="hs-stack-layer">Identity / Auth</span>
        <span class="hs-stack-owner">OAuth, WorkOS, MCP spec</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hs-stack-row">
        <span class="hs-stack-layer">Permission / Policy</span>
        <span class="hs-stack-owner">Permit.io, Cerbos, OPA, Cedar</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hs-stack-row hs-stack-row--highlight">
        <span class="hs-stack-layer">Trust Establishment</span>
        <span class="hs-stack-owner">Handshake</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hs-stack-row">
        <span class="hs-stack-layer">Execution / Action</span>
        <span class="hs-stack-owner">Stripe, MCP tools, APIs</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What it is / isn't -->
  <section class="hs-section">
    <div class="hs-section-label">Boundaries</div>
    <div class="hs-is-grid">
      <div class="hs-is-col">
        <h3>Handshake is</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Mutual trust verification before agent transactions</li>
          <li>Behavioral standing from weighted action history</li>
          <li>Human-in-the-loop escalation at architectural boundaries</li>
          <li>Offline-verifiable authorization artifacts</li>
          <li>Full audit trail — every decision reconstructible</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="hs-is-col">
        <h3>Handshake is not</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>A vault or secrets manager</li>
          <li>A replacement for OAuth or your identity provider</li>
          <li>A static permission check (allow/deny is commodity)</li>
          <li>An autonomous decision-maker</li>
          <li>The solution to the entire agentic economy</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Essay cross-link -->
  <section class="hs-section">
    <div class="hs-section-label">The Diagnosis</div>
    <div class="hs-prose">
      <h2>Read The Agentic Economy</h2>
      <p>
        A six-part whitepaper series on the structural shift from human-speed institutions
        to machine-speed economic actors. The essays establish the coordination gap that
        Handshake is designed to fill.
      </p>
      <div class="hs-essay-link-row">
        <a
          class="cta-link cta-link--primary"
          href="/entry"
          data-track-event="cta_click"
          data-track-location="handshake_crosslink"
          data-track-target="entry_essay"
        >
          Read the entry essay
        </a>
        <a
          class="cta-link"
          href="/"
          data-track-event="cta_click"
          data-track-location="handshake_crosslink"
          data-track-target="series_index"
        >
          View the full series
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Final waitlist CTA -->
  <section class="hs-section hs-section--final">
    <div class="hs-final-cta">
      <h2>We wrote the diagnosis.<br>Now we're building the infrastructure.</h2>
      <p>
        Handshake is pre-production. Join the waitlist to be notified when the
        mutual trust protocol is ready for integration.
      </p>
      <form class="hs-waitlist-form" id="waitlist-form-final" data-endpoint="/api/waitlist">
        <div class="hs-waitlist-row">
          <input
            type="email"
            name="email"
            required
            placeholder="you@company.com"
            class="hs-waitlist-input"
            autocomplete="email"
          />
          <button type="submit" class="cta-link cta-link--primary hs-waitlist-btn">
            Join the waitlist
          </button>
        </div>
        <p class="hs-waitlist-status" aria-live="polite"></p>
      </form>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  /* ─── Handshake page styles ──────────────────────────────────────────── */

  .hs-hero {
    padding: var(--space-4xl) 0 var(--space-3xl);
    max-width: 860px;
  }

  .hs-hero-eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--ui);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
  }

  .hs-hero-eyebrow::before {
    content: '';
    width: 40px;
    height: 2px;
    background: var(--accent);
  }

  .hs-hero-title {
    font-family: var(--display);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4.5vw, 3.25rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-xl);
  }

  .hs-hero-title-em {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .hs-hero-sub {
    font-family: var(--body);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2vw, 1.35rem);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--muted);
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-xl);
  }

  /* ─── Waitlist form ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── */

  .hs-waitlist-form {
    max-width: 480px;
  }

  .hs-waitlist-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .hs-waitlist-input {
    flex: 1;
    min-height: 48px;
    padding: 12px 16px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-right: none;
    background: var(--bg-alt);
    color: var(--text);
    font-family: var(--ui);
    font-size: 14px;
    transition: border-color 120ms ease-out;
  }

  .hs-waitlist-input::placeholder {
    color: var(--subtle);
  }

  .hs-waitlist-input:focus {
    border-color: var(--accent);
    outline: 2px solid var(--accent);
    outline-offset: -2px;
  }

  .hs-waitlist-btn {
    white-space: nowrap;
    border-left: none;
    box-shadow: none;
  }

  .hs-waitlist-btn:hover {
    transform: none;
    box-shadow: none;
  }

  .hs-waitlist-status {
    font-family: var(--ui);
    font-size: 12px;
    margin: var(--space-xs) 0 0;
    min-height: 1.4em;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .hs-waitlist-status[data-state="success"] {
    color: var(--success);
  }

  .hs-waitlist-status[data-state="error"] {
    color: var(--error);
  }

  /* ─── Sections ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */

  .hs-section {
    padding: var(--space-3xl) 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    position: relative;
  }

  .hs-section-label {
    font-family: var(--ui);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
  }

  .hs-section-label::before {
    content: '';
    width: 24px;
    height: 2px;
    background: var(--accent);
  }

  .hs-prose {
    max-width: 680px;
  }

  .hs-prose h2 {
    font-family: var(--display);
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.25rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-lg);
  }

  .hs-prose p {
    font-family: var(--body);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0 0 1.25em;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .hs-prose code {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.9em;
    color: var(--accent);
    background: var(--bg-alt);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  /* ─── Distinction (allowed vs trusted) ───────────────────────────────── */

  .hs-distinction {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .hs-distinction-item p {
    font-family: var(--body);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .hs-distinction-label {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--display);
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .hs-distinction-label--accent {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .hs-distinction-divider {
    width: 1px;
    align-self: stretch;
    background: var(--border);
  }

  /* ─── Phases ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */

  .hs-phases {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .hs-phase {
    padding: var(--space-xl);
    background: var(--bg-alt);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    position: relative;
  }

  .hs-phase::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 3px;
    background: var(--accent);
    transform: scaleX(0);
    transform-origin: left;
    transition: transform 500ms var(--ease-heavy);
  }

  .hs-phase:hover::after {
    transform: scaleX(1);
  }

  .hs-phase-num {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--ui);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--subtle);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .hs-phase-title {
    font-family: var(--display);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-sm);
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .hs-phase-desc {
    font-family: var(--body);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .hs-phase-desc code {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.85em;
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  /* ─── Architecture grid ──────────────────────────────────────────────── */

  .hs-arch-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .hs-arch-item {
    padding: var(--space-xl) 0;
    border-top: 2px solid var(--accent);
  }

  .hs-arch-item h3 {
    font-family: var(--display);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-sm);
  }

  .hs-arch-item p {
    font-family: var(--body);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  /* ─── Stack diagram ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── */

  .hs-stack {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .hs-stack-row {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    padding: var(--space-md) var(--space-lg);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    font-family: var(--ui);
    font-size: 13px;
  }

  .hs-stack-row:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .hs-stack-row--highlight {
    background: var(--accent);
    color: #fff;
    border-bottom-color: var(--accent-strong);
  }

  .hs-stack-layer {
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  .hs-stack-owner {
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .hs-stack-row--highlight .hs-stack-owner {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85);
  }

  /* ─── Is / Isn't grid ────────────────────────────────────────────────── */

  .hs-is-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-2xl);
    max-width: 860px;
  }

  .hs-is-col h3 {
    font-family: var(--display);
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-md);
  }

  .hs-is-col ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .hs-is-col li {
    font-family: var(--body);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    padding: var(--space-xs) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .hs-is-col li:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  /* ─── Essay cross-link ───────────────────────────────────────────────── */

  .hs-essay-link-row {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
  }

  /* ─── Final CTA ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */

  .hs-section--final {
    border-top: none;
    padding-bottom: var(--space-4xl);
  }

  .hs-final-cta {
    max-width: 680px;
    padding: var(--space-2xl);
    background: var(--bg-alt);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--accent);
  }

  .hs-final-cta h2 {
    font-family: var(--display);
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-md);
  }

  .hs-final-cta p {
    font-family: var(--body);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-xl);
  }

  /* ─── Responsive ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .hs-phases,
    .hs-arch-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .hs-distinction {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .hs-distinction-divider {
      width: 100%;
      height: 1px;
    }

    .hs-is-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-xl);
    }
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .hs-phase::after {
      transition: none;
    }

    .hs-phase:hover::after {
      transform: scaleX(1);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .hs-hero {
      padding: var(--space-3xl) 0 var(--space-2xl);
    }

    .hs-waitlist-row {
      flex-direction: column;
    }

    .hs-waitlist-input {
      border-right: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-bottom: none;
    }

    .hs-waitlist-btn {
      border-left: 1px solid var(--accent-strong);
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
  document.querySelectorAll<HTMLFormElement>(".hs-waitlist-form").forEach((form) => {
    form.addEventListener("submit", async (e) => {
      e.preventDefault();
      const statusEl = form.querySelector<HTMLParagraphElement>(".hs-waitlist-status");
      const emailInput = form.querySelector<HTMLInputElement>("input[name='email']");
      const email = emailInput?.value?.trim();

      if (!email || !statusEl) return;

      statusEl.textContent = "Submitting…";
      statusEl.removeAttribute("data-state");

      try {
        const endpoint = form.dataset.endpoint ?? "/api/waitlist";
        const res = await fetch(endpoint, {
          method: "POST",
          headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
          body: JSON.stringify({ email }),
        });

        if (res.ok) {
          statusEl.textContent = "You're on the list. We'll be in touch.";
          statusEl.setAttribute("data-state", "success");
          if (emailInput) emailInput.value = "";
        } else {
          const data = await res.json().catch(() => ({}));
          statusEl.textContent = data.error ?? "Something went wrong. Try again.";
          statusEl.setAttribute("data-state", "error");
        }
      } catch {
        statusEl.textContent = "Network error. Try again.";
        statusEl.setAttribute("data-state", "error");
      }
    });
  });
</script>
